---
title: Jarvis multi-replica — failover sequence
config:
  theme: neutral
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant AM as Alertmanager
    participant PG as PostgreSQL
    participant A as Pod A (leader)
    participant B as Pod B (follower)
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API

    Note over A,B: Steady state
    A->>PG: pg_try_advisory_lock (held)
    loop every JARVIS_POLL_INTERVAL
        A->>AM: poll alerts + silences
        A->>PG: persist snapshot + NOTIFY jarvis_snapshot
        PG-->>B: notification
        B->>PG: GetSnapshot(cluster)
        B->>B: merge into own AlertStore/SilenceStore
    end
    B->>PG: retry pg_try_advisory_lock every 5s (fails — held by A)

    Note over A: Pod A killed / evicted / node dies
    A--xPG: connection lost
    PG->>PG: session ends, advisory lock released

    Note over B: within ~5s (retry interval)<br/>or ~15-20s (hard node failure, TCP keepalive bound)
    B->>PG: pg_try_advisory_lock — acquired
    PG-->>B: promoted
    B->>K8s: PATCH pod label jarvis.kj187.de/role=leader
    B->>PG: reconcileStartupResolves (catch-up)
    B->>AM: poll alerts + silences
    B->>PG: persist snapshot + NOTIFY jarvis_snapshot

    Note over B: Pod B is now leader — polling,<br/>writing history, persisting snapshots
